This paper deals with a game-theoretic problem of facility location, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves locating a facility on a closed interval, which can be modeled as a data structure problem (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the design of strategyproof mechanisms, which is a topic in mechanism design and social choice theory (cs.AI, cs.EC). Finally, the paper provides approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and machine learning (cs.LG).
